2star  aIn recent years research on comparative typology has led to reveal regularities and to formulate new constraints upon variation for a broad range of phenomena. As the amount of typological research increased, a growing interest arose for the implications that findings in the typological field might have on second language acquisition. Written by experts in the field of typology and/or second language acquisition, this volume addresses theoretical and empirical issues on structural domains such as relative clauses and possessive constructions as well as pragmatic considerations on information organization in learners productions.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aSecond language acquisition. 0aTypology (Linguistics). 4aAufsatzsammlung. 4aFremdsprachenlernen. 4aSprachtypologie. 7aLANGUAGE ARTS & DISCIPLINES / Linguistics / General.2bisacsh1 aBernini, Giuliano, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarroll, Mary, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aComrie, Bernard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiannini, Stefania, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHammarberg, Björn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHendriks, Henriëtte, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKoptjevskaja-Tamm, Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMatthews, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNishi, Yumiko, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRamat, Anna Giacalone, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRamat, Anna Giacalone, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/e